HEADWORD: Tantalite
<hw>Tan"ta*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tantalite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A heavy mineral of
an iron-black color and submetallic luster. It is essentially a
tantalate of iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

